cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with detecting backdoor attacks on deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves analyzing the output of the network, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper introduces a new technique for detecting backdoor attacks, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves training and testing on benchmark datasets, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
